{
  "texts": [
    "Similarly, the predictive algorithms built by Yu et al. (2020) for undergraduate course grades and average GPA recorded better performance for male students than female students.",
    "In addition, a SpeechRater system for automated scoring of language assessment had to lower accuracy for students with speech impairment (Loukina & Buzick, 2017).",
    "Indeed, for AI applications to have a positive impact on education, it is crucial that their design considers fairness at every step (Suresh & Guttag, 2021; Gusenbauer & Haddaway, 2020).",
    "In response to these challenges, the Learning Analytics and AIED research community has increasingly focused on fairness, equity, and responsibility.",
    "Recent studies have begun to address these issues more directly."
  ]
}